/**
 * database.types.ts
 *
 * In a real project, the top-level Database interface is generated by the
 * Supabase CLI:  npx supabase gen types typescript --project-id <id> > src/shared/types/database.types.ts
 *
 * You commit this file and regenerate it whenever the schema changes.
 * This makes every Supabase query fully typed — column names, return shapes,
 * filter values. A typo in a column name is a compile error, not a runtime bug.
 *
 * The hand-written domain types below (Profile, AnalyticsEvent, etc.)
 * derive from the generated types via the helper utilities at the bottom.
 * This means they stay in sync with the DB automatically.
 */

